Containers sync to external registries
Use cmd/syncer.

build
go build cmd/syncer/syncer.go
Config
cp .env.example .env
Then edit file to enter credentials for harbor and target registry.

Run
To sync to remote github organization snps-scm4, run:

./syncer -container-list-file containers-without-sda.txt -registry-name snps-scm4 -registry-type github
containers.txt is file containing the list of containers to sync, in harbor.

Extraction Silicon.da container list from revision
Use cmd/get-containers

build
go build cmd/get-containers/get-containers.go
Run
./get-containers -siliconda 2024071_72_c1bf764e9e5 -pool-path pools/default
You can add new pool in pools in order to define some pool specific kustomization.

Usual use case
./get-containers -siliconda 2024071_72_c1bf764e9e5 -pool-path pools/default > containers.txt
./syncer -container-list-file containers.txt -registry-name snps-scm4 -registry-type github
